WEBVTT

1
00:03:23.840 --> 00:03:27.276
Stardate 9521.6.

2
00:03:27.480 --> 00:03:32.235
Captain's log U.S.S. Excelsior.
Hikaru Sulu commanding.

3
00:03:32.440 --> 00:03:37.116
After three years I've concluded my first
assignment as master of this vessel-

4
00:03:37.320 --> 00:03:41.871
- cataloguing gaseous planetary
anomalies in Beta Quadrant.

5
00:03:43.000 --> 00:03:45.912
We're heading home
under full impulse power.

6
00:03:46.120 --> 00:03:48.680
I'm pleased to report that ship and
crew have functioned well.

7
00:03:48.880 --> 00:03:53.032
According to this. we've completed
our survey of the entire sector.

8
00:04:04.400 --> 00:04:06.914
I have an energy wave at
240 degrees mark six port.

9
00:04:07.120 --> 00:04:08.678
Visual!

10
00:04:09.920 --> 00:04:12.195
My... God!

11
00:04:16.040 --> 00:04:17.519
Shields. Shields!

12
00:04:27.520 --> 00:04:29.112
She's not answering her helm.

13
00:04:29.320 --> 00:04:32.039
Starboard thrusters.
Turn her into the wave.

14
00:04:36.040 --> 00:04:38.429
Go to impulse power.

15
00:04:44.840 --> 00:04:48.389
- Damage report.
- Checking all systems.

16
00:04:54.880 --> 00:04:57.678
- That was no meteor shower.
- Negative. sir.

17
00:04:57.880 --> 00:05:02.431
The sub-space shock-wave
originated at bearing 323.75.

18
00:05:02.640 --> 00:05:06.553
Location... It's Praxis. sir.
It's a Klingon moon.

19
00:05:06.760 --> 00:05:10.673
Praxis is their
key energy production facility.

20
00:05:12.640 --> 00:05:17.077
Send to Klingon High Command. "This
is Excelsior. a Federation Starship."

21
00:05:17.280 --> 00:05:20.636
"We have monitored
a large explosion in your sector."

22
00:05:20.840 --> 00:05:24.196
- "Do you require assistance?"
- Aye. sir.

23
00:05:24.400 --> 00:05:28.916
- Mr Vultane. any more data?
- I've confirmed Praxis' location. but...

24
00:05:30.240 --> 00:05:33.676
- I cannot confirm Praxis' existence.
- On screen.

25
00:05:35.280 --> 00:05:38.397
- Magnify.
- Computer enhancement.

26
00:05:40.600 --> 00:05:42.750
- Praxis?
- What's left of it. sir.

27
00:05:42.960 --> 00:05:45.315
Captain. I'm getting a message
from Praxis.

28
00:05:45.520 --> 00:05:47.397
Let's have it.

29
00:05:59.480 --> 00:06:03.029
This is Brigadier Kerla.
speaking for the High Command.

30
00:06:03.240 --> 00:06:06.471
There has been an incident on Praxis.

31
00:06:06.680 --> 00:06:12.198
However. everything is under control.
We have no need for assistance.

32
00:06:12.400 --> 00:06:18.669
Obey treaty stipulations
and remain outside the Neutral Zone.

33
00:06:18.880 --> 00:06:23.078
This transmission ends now.

34
00:06:23.280 --> 00:06:25.999
- An incident?
- Do we report this. sir?

35
00:06:26.200 --> 00:06:27.713
Are you kidding?

36
00:06:34.880 --> 00:06:38.555
- What are we doing here?
- Maybe it's a retirement party.

37
00:06:38.760 --> 00:06:40.478
That suits me. I just bought a boat.

38
00:06:40.680 --> 00:06:44.639
I'm supposed to be chairing
a seminar at the Academy.

39
00:06:44.840 --> 00:06:48.389
- Isn't this just for top brass?
- Where is Sulu?

40
00:06:48.600 --> 00:06:52.832
Captain Sulu?
On assignment. Where's Spock?

41
00:07:00.320 --> 00:07:05.110
This briefing is classified.
Ladies and gentlemen. the C-in-C.

42
00:07:10.760 --> 00:07:12.955
As you were.

43
00:07:15.640 --> 00:07:18.200
I'll break
this information down succinctly.

44
00:07:18.400 --> 00:07:21.836
The Klingon empire
has 50 years of life left.

45
00:07:22.840 --> 00:07:28.278
For full details. I'm turning this briefing
over to Federation Special Envoy.

46
00:07:40.040 --> 00:07:41.758
Good morning.

47
00:07:41.960 --> 00:07:47.751
Two months ago a Federation Starship
monitored an explosion on Praxis.

48
00:07:47.960 --> 00:07:52.476
We believe it was caused by over-mining
and insufficient safety precautions.

49
00:07:52.680 --> 00:07:56.275
The moon's decimation means
deadly pollution of their ozone.

50
00:07:56.480 --> 00:08:01.315
They will have depleted
their oxygen supply in 50 Earth years.

51
00:08:02.600 --> 00:08:04.238
Due to their enormous military budget -

52
00:08:04.440 --> 00:08:09.833
- the Klingon economy doesn't have the
resources to combat this catastrophe.

53
00:08:10.040 --> 00:08:13.555
Last month. at the behest of
the Vulcan Ambassador. -

54
00:08:13.760 --> 00:08:19.357
- I opened a dialogue with Gorkon.
Chancellor of the Klingon High Council.

55
00:08:19.560 --> 00:08:23.269
He proposes to
commence negotiations at once.

56
00:08:23.480 --> 00:08:26.074
Negotiations for what?

57
00:08:26.280 --> 00:08:29.829
The dismantling of our space stations
and bases along the Neutral Zone. -

58
00:08:30.040 --> 00:08:35.910
- an end to 70 years of hostility.
which the Klingons can no longer afford.

59
00:08:36.120 --> 00:08:39.999
Bill. are we talking about
mothballing the Starfleet?

60
00:08:40.720 --> 00:08:45.032
Our exploration and scientific programs
would be unaffected. but...

61
00:08:45.240 --> 00:08:46.593
I must protest!

62
00:08:46.800 --> 00:08:50.839
To offer Klingons safe haven
within Federation space is suicide.

63
00:08:51.040 --> 00:08:53.998
Klingons would become
the alien trash of the galaxy.

64
00:08:54.200 --> 00:08:55.679
If we dismantle the fleet. -

65
00:08:55.880 --> 00:09:00.317
- we'd be defenceless before
an aggressive species on our territory.

66
00:09:00.520 --> 00:09:04.274
The opportunity here is
to bring them to their knees.

67
00:09:04.480 --> 00:09:08.234
Then we'll be in a better position
to dictate terms.

68
00:09:08.960 --> 00:09:12.032
- Sir...
- Captain Kirk?

69
00:09:12.240 --> 00:09:16.153
The Klingons
have never been trustworthy.

70
00:09:16.360 --> 00:09:20.353
I agree with Admiral Cartwright.
This is a terrifying idea.

71
00:09:20.560 --> 00:09:24.792
It is imperative that we act now
to support the Gorkon initiative. -

72
00:09:25.000 --> 00:09:27.958
- lest more conservative elements
persuade his empire -

73
00:09:28.160 --> 00:09:31.596
- that it's better to attempt
a military solution and die fighting.

74
00:09:31.800 --> 00:09:34.837
You. Captain Kirk.
are to be our first olive branch.

75
00:09:36.440 --> 00:09:41.036
We are to rendezvous with the vessel
which is bringing Gorkon to Earth -

76
00:09:41.240 --> 00:09:43.959
- and to escort him safely through
Federation space.

77
00:09:44.520 --> 00:09:46.112
Me?

78
00:09:46.320 --> 00:09:51.917
There are Klingons who feel the same
about the peace treaty as yourself. -

79
00:09:52.120 --> 00:09:55.430
- but they'll think twice about attacking
the Enterprise under your command.

80
00:09:55.640 --> 00:09:58.791
I have personally vouched for you
in this matter.

81
00:09:59.400 --> 00:10:02.472
You have personally vouched?

82
00:10:03.360 --> 00:10:07.990
You will extend Chancellor Gorkon
full diplomatic courtesy. Captain.

83
00:10:08.200 --> 00:10:12.079
- A full Ambassador is better equipped...
- If there's no further business...

84
00:10:12.800 --> 00:10:16.554
...I wish you and your crew Godspeed.
Thank you. ladies and gentlemen.

85
00:10:16.760 --> 00:10:19.718
I remind you this meeting is classified.

86
00:10:25.600 --> 00:10:29.798
I don't know whether to
congratulate you or not. Jim.

87
00:10:30.000 --> 00:10:31.991
I wouldn't.

88
00:10:35.120 --> 00:10:36.997
We volunteered?

89
00:10:37.200 --> 00:10:41.955
There's an old Vulcan proverb.
"Only Nixon could go to China."

90
00:10:43.200 --> 00:10:45.919
How could you vouch for me?

91
00:10:46.120 --> 00:10:50.636
- That's arrogant presumption.
- My father requested that I open...

92
00:10:50.840 --> 00:10:56.073
I know your father is the Vulcan
Ambassador. but you know how I feel.

93
00:10:57.720 --> 00:11:00.029
- They're animals.
- Jim...

94
00:11:00.240 --> 00:11:05.234
- There is an historic opportunity here.
- Don't believe them! Don't trust them.

95
00:11:05.920 --> 00:11:08.480
- They're dying.
- Let them die.

96
00:11:11.400 --> 00:11:16.474
Has it occurred to you that this crew is
due to stand down in three months?

97
00:11:16.680 --> 00:11:19.194
We've done our bit for king and country.

98
00:11:20.160 --> 00:11:21.991
You should have trusted me.

99
00:11:27.880 --> 00:11:31.634
Control. this is S-D 103.
approach to Space dock. Over.

100
00:11:31.840 --> 00:11:39.076
You are clear to deliver Captain Kirk
and party to N.C.C. 1701 Alpha.

101
00:11:43.960 --> 00:11:47.316
- Captain on the bridge!
- As you were. Lieutenant?

102
00:11:47.520 --> 00:11:51.991
Val'eris. sir. We were told you needed
a helmsman. so I volunteered.

103
00:11:52.960 --> 00:11:55.030
It is agreeable to see you again.

104
00:11:55.240 --> 00:11:59.313
She was the first Vulcan to graduate
at the top of her class at the Academy.

105
00:11:59.520 --> 00:12:02.671
- You must be very proud.
- I don't believe so. sir.

106
00:12:02.880 --> 00:12:04.313
She's a Vulcan. alright.

107
00:12:04.880 --> 00:12:08.316
Let's get this over with.
Departure stations.

108
00:12:08.520 --> 00:12:12.479
- Scotty? Did you find the engine room?
- Right where I left it.

109
00:12:12.680 --> 00:12:15.399
Stand by.
Uhura. get me the dock master.

110
00:12:15.600 --> 00:12:17.158
Control tower reading. sir.

111
00:12:17.640 --> 00:12:21.918
Control. this is Enterprise
requesting permission to depart.

112
00:12:22.120 --> 00:12:26.830
This is Control. Permission to depart
granted. 30 seconds for port gates.

113
00:12:27.040 --> 00:12:31.272
- Clear all moorings.
- Awaiting port gates from this mark.

114
00:12:31.480 --> 00:12:34.153
- All lines clear.
- Aft thrusters.

115
00:12:34.360 --> 00:12:37.557
Thank you. Lieutenant.
1 quarter impulse power.

116
00:12:37.760 --> 00:12:42.515
Captain. regulations specify
thrusters only while in space dock.

117
00:12:47.040 --> 00:12:48.439
Jim...

118
00:12:50.680 --> 00:12:52.796
You heard the order. Lieutenant.

119
00:12:53.720 --> 00:12:55.950
Aye. sir.

120
00:13:27.000 --> 00:13:30.549
Captain's log. Stardate 9522.6.

121
00:13:30.760 --> 00:13:35.959
I've never trusted Klingons.
and I never will.

122
00:13:39.160 --> 00:13:42.869
I can never forgive them for
the death of my boy.

123
00:13:44.160 --> 00:13:51.157
To escort the Chancellor of the Klingon
High Council to a peace summit -

124
00:13:51.360 --> 00:13:54.079
- is problematic. at best.

125
00:13:57.000 --> 00:14:01.676
Spock says this could be an historic
occasion. I'd like to believe him.

126
00:14:01.880 --> 00:14:06.715
But how on Earth can history get past
people like me?

127
00:14:08.080 --> 00:14:11.311
- Sorry.
- You could have knocked.

128
00:14:11.520 --> 00:14:16.640
We are almost at the rendezvous. sir.
I thought that you would like to know.

129
00:14:20.720 --> 00:14:25.111
Permission to speak freely. sir.
It is an honour to serve with you.

130
00:14:30.600 --> 00:14:33.160
You piloted well out of space dock.
Lieutenant.

131
00:14:34.080 --> 00:14:36.196
I've always wanted to try that.

132
00:14:46.160 --> 00:14:48.515
You've done well. Val'eris.

133
00:14:48.720 --> 00:14:54.556
As your sponsor at the Academy I've
followed your career with satisfaction.

134
00:14:54.760 --> 00:14:58.958
And as a Vulcan.
you have exceeded my expectations.

135
00:15:00.600 --> 00:15:03.876
I do not understand this representation.

136
00:15:04.080 --> 00:15:08.471
It's a depiction
from ancient Earth mythology.

137
00:15:08.680 --> 00:15:10.079
"The expulsion from Paradise."

138
00:15:10.280 --> 00:15:16.276
- Why keep it in your quarters?
- To remind me that all things end.

139
00:15:20.800 --> 00:15:26.352
It is of endings that I wish to speak.

140
00:15:26.560 --> 00:15:29.791
Sir. I address you
as a kindred intellect.

141
00:15:30.880 --> 00:15:33.553
Do you not recognise...

142
00:15:33.760 --> 00:15:37.309
...that a turning point has been reached
in the affairs of the Federation?

143
00:15:39.440 --> 00:15:44.912
History is replete with turning points.
You must have faith.

144
00:15:45.120 --> 00:15:49.079
- Faith?
- The universe will unfold as it should.

145
00:15:50.120 --> 00:15:55.797
- Is that logical? Surely we must...
- Logic. logic. logic.

146
00:15:56.000 --> 00:16:03.076
Logic is the beginning of wisdom.
Val'eris. Not the end.

147
00:16:03.960 --> 00:16:07.589
This will be my final voyage on board
this vessel as a member of her crew.

148
00:16:11.160 --> 00:16:15.039
Nature abhors a vacuum.

149
00:16:15.240 --> 00:16:18.312
I intend you to replace me.

150
00:16:26.040 --> 00:16:28.998
I could only succeed you. sir.

151
00:16:33.160 --> 00:16:35.754
Now hear this.
All officers to the bridge.

152
00:16:35.960 --> 00:16:40.033
Klingon battle cruiser off the port bow.
All Officers to the bridge.

153
00:16:56.040 --> 00:16:58.349
Captain on the bridge!

154
00:17:11.400 --> 00:17:13.675
Shall we raise our shields. Captain?

155
00:17:15.320 --> 00:17:17.550
I've never been this close.

156
00:17:19.520 --> 00:17:22.751
The Chancellor is undoubtedly
awaiting our signal.

157
00:17:31.520 --> 00:17:34.512
- Uhura. hailing frequencies.
- Aye. sir.

158
00:17:34.720 --> 00:17:36.915
Right standard rudder.
Bring us alongside.

159
00:17:37.120 --> 00:17:39.873
Right standard rudder.
Z plus 5 degrees.

160
00:17:40.080 --> 00:17:42.674
Channel is open. Captain.

161
00:17:42.880 --> 00:17:46.919
This is the Starship Enterprise.
Captain James T. Kirk commanding.

162
00:17:47.480 --> 00:17:52.998
This is Kronos One.
I am Chancellor Gorkon.

163
00:17:57.080 --> 00:18:02.200
We've been ordered to escort you
to your meeting on Earth.

164
00:18:02.400 --> 00:18:03.799
Thank you.

165
00:18:04.560 --> 00:18:09.873
Would you and your party care to dine
this evening aboard the Enterprise -

166
00:18:10.080 --> 00:18:12.514
- as guests of
the United Federation of Planets?

167
00:18:12.720 --> 00:18:17.350
We would be delighted to accept
your gracious invitation.

168
00:18:19.480 --> 00:18:22.597
We'll make arrangements to have you
beamed aboard at 19:30 hours.

169
00:18:23.160 --> 00:18:25.037
I shall look forward to that.

170
00:18:32.200 --> 00:18:34.156
I hope you're happy.

171
00:18:34.360 --> 00:18:37.989
Captain! There is a supply of
Romulan ale aboard.

172
00:18:38.200 --> 00:18:41.237
It might make
the evening pass more... smoothly.

173
00:18:41.800 --> 00:18:44.234
Officer thinking. Lieutenant.

174
00:18:46.320 --> 00:18:48.072
Guess who's coming to dinner.

175
00:18:59.520 --> 00:19:01.431
Energize.

176
00:19:33.640 --> 00:19:35.710
- Chancellor Gorkon.
- Captain Kirk.

177
00:19:35.920 --> 00:19:38.832
May I present Captain Spock.
whom I believe you know.

178
00:19:39.040 --> 00:19:43.909
Captain. face to face at last.
You have my thanks.

179
00:19:44.120 --> 00:19:47.192
Chancellor.

180
00:19:47.400 --> 00:19:49.391
Gentlemen.

181
00:19:49.600 --> 00:19:52.478
This is my daughter. Azetbur...

182
00:19:55.880 --> 00:20:01.000
My military advisor. Brigadier Kerla...

183
00:20:01.200 --> 00:20:04.795
...and this is General Chang.
my chief of staff.

184
00:20:05.000 --> 00:20:08.072
I have so wanted to meet you. Captain.

185
00:20:09.160 --> 00:20:14.598
- I'm not sure how to take that.
- Sincere admiration. Kirk.

186
00:20:14.800 --> 00:20:17.792
From one warrior to another.

187
00:20:19.240 --> 00:20:21.959
Right...

188
00:20:23.400 --> 00:20:27.791
This way. You might enjoy a brief tour.

189
00:20:44.080 --> 00:20:46.548
- They all look alike.
- What about that smell?

190
00:20:46.760 --> 00:20:51.515
You know only top of the line models
can even talk...

191
00:20:55.200 --> 00:20:57.760
- You men have work?
- Yes. ma'am.

192
00:20:57.960 --> 00:21:00.076
Then snap to it.

193
00:21:37.520 --> 00:21:39.272
I offer a toast.

194
00:21:40.040 --> 00:21:43.237
The undiscovered country.

195
00:21:45.520 --> 00:21:48.353
- The future.
- The undiscovered country.

196
00:21:48.560 --> 00:21:50.630
Hamlet. act 3. scene 1.

197
00:21:50.840 --> 00:21:54.913
You have not experienced Shake-
speare until you've read him in Klingon.

198
00:22:05.400 --> 00:22:09.313
Captain Kirk.
I thought Romulan ale was illegal.

199
00:22:09.520 --> 00:22:13.274
An advantage of being 1.000 light
years from Federation headquarters.

200
00:22:14.280 --> 00:22:18.034
To you. Chancellor Gorkon.
One of the architects of our future.

201
00:22:18.240 --> 00:22:19.753
Chancellor!

202
00:22:22.160 --> 00:22:25.357
Perhaps we are looking at
something of that future here.

203
00:22:28.280 --> 00:22:35.072
Tell me. Captain Kirk. Would you
be willing to give up Starfleet?

204
00:22:38.880 --> 00:22:44.989
The Captain feels that Starfleet's
mission has always been one of peace.

205
00:22:48.160 --> 00:22:52.073
I wouldn't dispute my first officer.
Starfleet has always been...

206
00:22:52.280 --> 00:22:57.115
There's no need to mince words.
In space. all warriors are cold warriors.

207
00:22:59.480 --> 00:23:04.429
General.
are you fond of... Shakespeare?

208
00:23:05.200 --> 00:23:09.910
We believe all planets have a sovereign
claim to inalienable human rights.

209
00:23:10.120 --> 00:23:14.910
"Inalien..."
If you could only hear yourselves.

210
00:23:15.120 --> 00:23:20.240
"Human rights."
Why. the very name is racist.

211
00:23:20.440 --> 00:23:24.115
The Federation is
a "homo sapiens only" club.

212
00:23:24.320 --> 00:23:27.073
Present company excepted. of course.

213
00:23:27.280 --> 00:23:32.513
We know where this is leading -
the annihilation of our culture.

214
00:23:32.720 --> 00:23:35.996
That's not true. No!

215
00:23:36.200 --> 00:23:41.718
"To be or not to be"...That is the
question which preoccupies our people.

216
00:23:41.920 --> 00:23:45.151
- We need breathing room.
- Earth. Hitler. 1938.

217
00:23:47.120 --> 00:23:49.076
I beg your pardon.

218
00:23:52.800 --> 00:23:54.677
Well...

219
00:23:56.920 --> 00:23:59.832
I see we have a long way to go.

220
00:24:00.400 --> 00:24:03.870
We must do this again sometime.

221
00:24:06.960 --> 00:24:12.159
You don't trust me. do you?
I don't blame you.

222
00:24:13.720 --> 00:24:16.188
If there is to be a brave new world. -

223
00:24:16.400 --> 00:24:22.077
- our generation is going to have
the hardest time living in it.

224
00:24:24.880 --> 00:24:29.078
- Captain Spock.
- Chancellor. Madam.

225
00:24:29.280 --> 00:24:31.157
Captain.

226
00:24:31.360 --> 00:24:33.874
Well. most kind.

227
00:24:34.080 --> 00:24:39.359
Parting is such sweet sorrow.
Hmm. Captain?

228
00:24:40.160 --> 00:24:43.994
"Have we not heard the chimes
at midnight?"

229
00:25:06.680 --> 00:25:09.240
Thank God!

230
00:25:09.440 --> 00:25:14.833
- Did you see the way they ate?
- Terrible table manners.

231
00:25:15.040 --> 00:25:19.079
I doubt our own behaviour will distinguish
us in the annals of diplomacy.

232
00:25:19.280 --> 00:25:23.671
I'm going to sleep this off. Is there any
other way we can screw up tonight?

233
00:25:23.880 --> 00:25:27.793
I'm going to go find
a pot of black coffee.

234
00:25:41.520 --> 00:25:47.789
The Enterprise hosted
Chancellor Gorkon to dinner last night.

235
00:25:48.000 --> 00:25:52.357
Our manners
weren't exactly Emily Post.

236
00:25:52.560 --> 00:26:00.035
To the galley - Romulan ale no longer
to be served at diplomatic functions.

237
00:26:00.240 --> 00:26:05.109
Captain Kirk. will you please
join me on the bridge? Captain Kirk?

238
00:26:11.120 --> 00:26:13.156
- Captain.
- What is it?

239
00:26:13.360 --> 00:26:16.158
- I find this curious.
- Spock. I'm really tired.

240
00:26:16.360 --> 00:26:20.956
We are reading an enormous amount of
neutron radiation.

241
00:26:21.160 --> 00:26:25.119
- Where?
- It appears to emanate from us.

242
00:26:25.320 --> 00:26:27.231
The Enterprise?

243
00:26:29.080 --> 00:26:34.598
Val'eris. do you know anything about
a radiation surge? Chekov?

244
00:26:34.800 --> 00:26:37.360
Only the size of my head.

245
00:26:38.000 --> 00:26:39.831
I know what you mean.

246
00:26:54.160 --> 00:26:57.516
- What's happened?
- We've fired on the Chancellor's ship.

247
00:26:57.720 --> 00:27:00.792
Torpedo room!
Please confirm. have we fired?

248
00:27:02.280 --> 00:27:04.396
- Uhura. monitor.
- Aye. sir.

249
00:27:04.600 --> 00:27:08.878
- Direct hit.
- Confirmed. sir.

250
00:27:19.200 --> 00:27:20.792
We've lost gravity!

251
00:27:34.800 --> 00:27:36.358
We are betrayed!

252
00:27:36.560 --> 00:27:40.269
This is the bridge. Do you read me?

253
00:27:40.480 --> 00:27:45.759
- Did we fire those torpedoes?
- Negative. We're still fully loaded.

254
00:28:03.680 --> 00:28:06.240
Find Chang.

255
00:28:12.560 --> 00:28:15.597
Unable to confirm or deny
firing the torpedoes.

256
00:28:15.800 --> 00:28:18.189
- Hailing frequencies.
- Aye. sir.

257
00:28:18.400 --> 00:28:21.710
Kronos One. this is Enterprise.
Do you read?

258
00:29:26.080 --> 00:29:31.313
It's very hard to make out. There's been
weapons firing and a lot of shouting.

259
00:29:31.760 --> 00:29:35.878
- She's still listing.
- She's spinning out of control.

260
00:29:53.960 --> 00:29:57.748
Restoring auxiliary gravity...

261
00:30:07.520 --> 00:30:11.149
Have you not
a shred of decency in you. Kirk?

262
00:30:11.360 --> 00:30:17.117
We come in peace.
and you blatantly defy that peace.

263
00:30:17.320 --> 00:30:19.629
For that.
I shall blow you out of the stars.

264
00:30:22.320 --> 00:30:25.915
- We haven't fired.
- Captain...

265
00:30:26.120 --> 00:30:29.635
According to our data banks.
we have. Twice...

266
00:30:29.840 --> 00:30:31.637
Captain. they're coming about.

267
00:30:38.320 --> 00:30:40.959
- They're preparing to fire.
- Shields up. Captain?

268
00:30:41.160 --> 00:30:44.516
- Captain. our shields.
- Shields up. Captain?

269
00:30:46.680 --> 00:30:49.035
Signal our surrender.

270
00:30:49.240 --> 00:30:50.593
We surrender!

271
00:30:51.800 --> 00:30:56.191
- This is Enterprise. We surrender.
- If they fire. with our shields down...

272
00:30:56.400 --> 00:31:00.552
...we will not be able to respond.
- Repeat. Enterprise surrenders.

273
00:31:03.840 --> 00:31:07.515
- Are we firing torpedoes?
- I wish I knew.

274
00:31:07.720 --> 00:31:11.872
- I'm going aboard. Spock. take the con.
- I involved you. I will go.

275
00:31:12.080 --> 00:31:18.155
No. I'll go. We'll not be the instigators
of war on the eve of universal peace.

276
00:31:18.360 --> 00:31:20.954
I'm going too. they may need a doctor.

277
00:31:21.160 --> 00:31:25.711
Uhura. tell them we're coming.
and tell them we're unarmed.

278
00:31:30.600 --> 00:31:33.876
- Have you lost your mind?!
- I don't understand what's happened.

279
00:31:34.080 --> 00:31:37.197
We're here to help.

280
00:31:37.400 --> 00:31:39.789
Follow me.

281
00:32:03.080 --> 00:32:07.551
- Chancellor Gorkon.
- My God! What has happened here?

282
00:32:07.760 --> 00:32:11.389
- You dare to feign ignorance?
- What happened?

283
00:32:11.600 --> 00:32:15.673
With a direct torpedo hit.
you crippled our gravitational field -

284
00:32:15.880 --> 00:32:20.670
- and two of your Starfleet crew beamed
aboard wearing magnetic boots.

285
00:32:20.880 --> 00:32:24.031
- Aren't you carrying a surgeon?
- We were until this disgrace.

286
00:32:24.240 --> 00:32:26.595
Then for god's sake. let me help.

287
00:32:37.520 --> 00:32:42.958
I've got a pulse - we can move him.
I need light. Put him on the table.

288
00:32:50.960 --> 00:32:54.919
Hold him! Hold him while I stabilize him.

289
00:33:00.600 --> 00:33:03.114
I said hold him!

290
00:33:06.280 --> 00:33:07.713
Sweet Jesus.

291
00:33:07.920 --> 00:33:10.878
- Can you?
- I don't even know his anatomy.

292
00:33:15.360 --> 00:33:17.635
- His wounds are not closing.
- He's killing him!

293
00:33:23.240 --> 00:33:26.357
He's gone into
some kind of damned arrest.

294
00:33:30.160 --> 00:33:32.549
Come on. dammit! Come on!

295
00:33:37.240 --> 00:33:39.276
He's not responding.

296
00:33:57.400 --> 00:34:01.029
Don't let it end this way. Captain.

297
00:34:35.680 --> 00:34:41.550
Under article 184 of your
Interstellar Law...

298
00:34:41.760 --> 00:34:44.035
...l'm placing you under arrest.

299
00:34:44.240 --> 00:34:49.519
You're charged with assassinating
the Chancellor of the High Council.

300
00:34:49.720 --> 00:34:52.473
He tried to save him.

301
00:34:57.960 --> 00:35:01.032
They've been arrested.

302
00:35:01.240 --> 00:35:04.915
Mr Spock. we've got to do something.

303
00:35:05.120 --> 00:35:08.157
I assume command of this ship
as of 02:30 hours.

304
00:35:08.360 --> 00:35:14.469
Commander Uhura. notify Starfleet
headquarters and request instructions.

305
00:35:14.680 --> 00:35:18.559
We cannot allow them
to be taken to Kronos as prisoners.

306
00:35:18.760 --> 00:35:23.197
Opening fire will not retrieve them.
and we must avoid an armed conflict.

307
00:35:23.400 --> 00:35:25.675
We will be able to follow
the Captain's movements.

308
00:35:25.880 --> 00:35:28.952
- How did you achieve this?
- Time is precious.

309
00:35:29.160 --> 00:35:32.391
We must piece together
what happened here tonight.

310
00:35:32.600 --> 00:35:36.036
According to our data bank.
this ship fired those torpedoes.

311
00:35:36.240 --> 00:35:40.677
- No way!
- I sympathize. but we need evidence.

312
00:35:40.880 --> 00:35:44.236
Please accompany me.

313
00:35:44.440 --> 00:35:48.228
And if we cannot piece together
what happened? What then. sir?

314
00:35:48.440 --> 00:35:52.479
In that case. Mr Chekov. it resides in
the purview of the diplomats.

315
00:35:54.400 --> 00:35:58.279
The Chancellor of
the High Council is dead!

316
00:35:58.480 --> 00:36:01.358
The result of an unprovoked attack -

317
00:36:01.560 --> 00:36:07.112
- while he travelled to see you under
a flag of truce on a mission of peace!

318
00:36:07.320 --> 00:36:10.471
Captain Kirk
was legally arrested for the crime.

319
00:36:10.680 --> 00:36:15.595
He and Dr. McCoy boarded
Kronos One of their own free will.

320
00:36:15.800 --> 00:36:20.749
- None of these facts are in dispute.
- I have ordered an investigation.

321
00:36:21.680 --> 00:36:23.750
- In the meantime...
- In the meantime...

322
00:36:23.960 --> 00:36:30.195
...we expect the Federation to abide by
the articles of Interstellar Law.

323
00:36:30.400 --> 00:36:35.155
Kirk and Dr. McCoy will stand trial for
the assassination of Chancellor Gorkon.

324
00:36:35.360 --> 00:36:39.797
Out of the question. Ambassador
Sarek. can we get them extradited?

325
00:36:40.400 --> 00:36:45.235
Mr President. I share a measure of
personal responsibility in this matter. -

326
00:36:45.440 --> 00:36:49.592
- but I am obliged to confirm my
esteemed colleagues legal interpretation.

327
00:36:49.800 --> 00:36:53.110
What is the position of
the Romulan government?

328
00:36:54.520 --> 00:36:56.750
I must concur with my colleagues.

329
00:36:56.960 --> 00:37:02.239
You can't believe that Kirk assassinated
the Chancellor of the High Council.

330
00:37:02.440 --> 00:37:06.752
Mr President.
I don't know what to believe.

331
00:37:07.520 --> 00:37:09.750
I'm waiting for your answer. sir.

332
00:37:11.960 --> 00:37:15.919
This President is not above the law.

333
00:37:20.000 --> 00:37:24.152
Mr President. Starfleet command
is here from San Francisco.

334
00:37:25.680 --> 00:37:27.750
- Mr President.
- Mr President.

335
00:37:27.960 --> 00:37:32.158
Bill. Admiral Cartwright.
please sit down.

336
00:37:34.400 --> 00:37:38.439
Mr President. we cannot allow
Federation citizens to be abducted.

337
00:37:38.640 --> 00:37:41.029
I'm constrained to observe
Interstellar Law.

338
00:37:41.240 --> 00:37:45.028
Sir. would you please
take a look at this.

339
00:37:48.960 --> 00:37:52.919
We prepared Operation Retrieve
based on the danger of terrorism -

340
00:37:53.120 --> 00:37:57.591
- between the Klingon empire
and the Federation.

341
00:37:57.800 --> 00:38:00.268
We can go in. rescue the hostages -

342
00:38:00.480 --> 00:38:05.235
- and get out in 24 hours with
acceptable losses.

343
00:38:05.440 --> 00:38:07.874
- We have the technology...
- Yes. yes.

344
00:38:08.080 --> 00:38:11.072
But suppose you precipitate
a full-scale war?

345
00:38:11.280 --> 00:38:14.716
Then. quite frankly.
we can clean their chronometers.

346
00:38:16.000 --> 00:38:21.597
Mr President. they are vulnerable.
There will never be a better time.

347
00:38:21.800 --> 00:38:25.873
The longer we wait. the less accessible
the hostages will be.

348
00:38:26.080 --> 00:38:30.278
I'll bear that in mind. Thank you.
gentlemen. that's all for now.

349
00:38:31.800 --> 00:38:34.394
Mr President.

350
00:38:44.560 --> 00:38:46.710
Sir...

351
00:38:48.080 --> 00:38:53.313
Those men have literally
saved this planet.

352
00:38:53.520 --> 00:38:56.557
And now they're going to save it again.

353
00:38:57.280 --> 00:38:59.350
By standing trial.

354
00:39:02.840 --> 00:39:05.513
Report back on the double.
Do you read?

355
00:39:05.720 --> 00:39:11.033
- We're to report back at once.
- We can't abandon Kirk and McCoy.

356
00:39:11.240 --> 00:39:16.473
400 years ago. on Earth. workers
who felt their livelyhood threatened -

357
00:39:16.680 --> 00:39:21.993
- flung their wooden shoes called
"sabots" into the machines to stop them.

358
00:39:24.120 --> 00:39:27.669
Hence the word "sabotage".

359
00:39:30.160 --> 00:39:35.109
We experience technical malfunction.
All back-up systems inoperative.

360
00:39:35.320 --> 00:39:38.517
Excellent. I mean... too bad.

361
00:39:39.800 --> 00:39:45.557
Mr President. I have been named
chancellor in my father's place.

362
00:39:45.760 --> 00:39:49.753
Madam Chancellor.
you have my condolences on your loss.

363
00:39:49.960 --> 00:39:53.794
I assure you
that this shameful deed will not...

364
00:39:54.000 --> 00:39:59.028
Let us come to the point. You want
this conference to go forward.

365
00:39:59.240 --> 00:40:02.471
I will attend in one week.
on one condition.

366
00:40:02.680 --> 00:40:08.869
We will not extradite the prisoners.
and you will not attempt to rescue them.

367
00:40:09.080 --> 00:40:12.959
We would consider any such attempt
an act of war.

368
00:40:13.160 --> 00:40:15.196
We hope you'll be our guest
here on Earth.

369
00:40:15.400 --> 00:40:20.190
After recent events. you will
understand if I prefer a neutral site.

370
00:40:20.400 --> 00:40:25.474
And in the interest of security. let us
keep the location secret for now.

371
00:40:25.680 --> 00:40:28.752
As you wish. Madam Chancellor.

372
00:40:30.000 --> 00:40:33.231
Attack them now. while we still can.

373
00:40:33.440 --> 00:40:37.035
Attack or be slaves in their world.

374
00:40:40.440 --> 00:40:44.069
We can take whole by force.
what they propose to divide.

375
00:40:44.880 --> 00:40:49.351
War is obsolete. General.

376
00:40:49.560 --> 00:40:54.634
As we are in danger of becoming.

377
00:40:54.840 --> 00:41:00.233
Better to die on our feet
than live on our knees.

378
00:41:00.440 --> 00:41:03.477
That wasn't what my father wanted.

379
00:41:03.680 --> 00:41:07.070
Your father was killed
for what he wanted.

380
00:41:07.760 --> 00:41:11.833
The peace process will go forward.

381
00:41:12.560 --> 00:41:14.278
Kirk...

382
00:41:17.560 --> 00:41:22.190
Kirk will pay for my father's death.

383
00:41:24.800 --> 00:41:29.954
It is as I said. Mr Spock.
Inventory registers every torpedo.

384
00:41:30.160 --> 00:41:32.674
Yet the data banks insist we fired.

385
00:41:32.880 --> 00:41:35.394
- One computer is lying.
- A computer doesn't lie!

386
00:41:35.600 --> 00:41:39.388
Precisely. Therefore we must inspect
each torpedo visually.

387
00:41:39.600 --> 00:41:42.672
That could take hours!
And if they're all there?

388
00:41:42.880 --> 00:41:46.156
Then someone forged an entry
in the data banks.

389
00:41:48.520 --> 00:41:51.876
Gorkon's daughter has been named
Chancellor. It was on the news.

390
00:41:52.080 --> 00:41:55.072
I'll bet that bitch killed her father.

391
00:41:55.280 --> 00:41:58.317
- Her own father?
- It is an old story. sir.

392
00:41:58.520 --> 00:42:03.469
They don't place the same value on life
as we do. you know that.

393
00:42:03.680 --> 00:42:07.116
Take my word.
she did not shed one bloody tear.

394
00:42:07.320 --> 00:42:10.676
Hardly conclusive.
since Klingons have no tear-ducts.

395
00:42:10.880 --> 00:42:14.589
Lieutenant. any response from Starfleet
since our dispatch?

396
00:42:14.800 --> 00:42:16.279
Yes. sir.

397
00:42:17.000 --> 00:42:18.831
And?

398
00:42:19.040 --> 00:42:22.350
Commander Uhura is experiencing
technical difficulties. sir.

399
00:42:25.000 --> 00:42:27.514
Curious. Very well.

400
00:42:27.720 --> 00:42:32.669
For 24 hours. we will agree
this conversation didn't take place.

401
00:42:32.880 --> 00:42:34.552
- A lie?
- An omission.

402
00:42:34.760 --> 00:42:38.116
In 24 hours we won't have a clue
where Captain Kirk is.

403
00:42:38.320 --> 00:42:41.869
- I know precisely where he will be.
- You do? Where?

404
00:42:44.400 --> 00:42:48.473
Kirk. Kirk. Kirk. Kirk...

405
00:43:10.000 --> 00:43:11.877
It's a damn show trial.

406
00:43:22.400 --> 00:43:26.916
The Enterprise fired on Kronos One
without provocation.

407
00:43:27.120 --> 00:43:28.917
The Chancellor and his advisors...

408
00:43:29.120 --> 00:43:31.714
...having been lulled into
a false sense of security -

409
00:43:31.920 --> 00:43:35.310
- by an invitation to a dinner
aboard Captain Kirk's vessel -

410
00:43:35.520 --> 00:43:39.479
- at precisely 19:30 hours
that same evening.

411
00:43:39.960 --> 00:43:42.076
Call your first witness.

412
00:43:42.280 --> 00:43:45.716
After the first shot
we lost our gravitational field.

413
00:43:45.920 --> 00:43:47.990
I was weightless and couldn't function.

414
00:43:48.200 --> 00:43:50.998
Then two Starfleet crewmen
came towards me.

415
00:43:51.200 --> 00:43:53.839
Or perhaps
they merely wore Starfleet uniforms.

416
00:43:54.040 --> 00:43:56.918
That remark is speculative.
I move that it be stricken.

417
00:43:57.120 --> 00:44:00.999
We're interested in facts. not theories.

418
00:44:01.640 --> 00:44:06.634
If the gravitational unit was not
functioning. how could they walk?

419
00:44:06.840 --> 00:44:09.070
They appeared to be wearing
magnetic boots.

420
00:44:11.720 --> 00:44:16.032
- Gravity boots?
- Dr. McCoy.

421
00:44:16.240 --> 00:44:19.949
Would you be so good as to tell me -

422
00:44:20.160 --> 00:44:23.914
- what is your current medical status?

423
00:44:24.120 --> 00:44:26.714
Aside from a touch of arthritis.
I'd say pretty good.

424
00:44:34.280 --> 00:44:36.589
You have a singular wit. Doctor.

425
00:44:36.800 --> 00:44:41.157
For 27 years I've been surgeon
aboard the U.S.S. Enterprise.

426
00:44:41.360 --> 00:44:46.309
In three months I stand down.

427
00:44:46.520 --> 00:44:48.238
You know...

428
00:44:48.440 --> 00:44:53.309
I believe that you consumed rather
a generous amount of Romulan ale -

429
00:44:53.520 --> 00:44:55.875
- in the officers mess
on the night in question.

430
00:44:56.080 --> 00:44:57.991
- Objection.
- Sustained.

431
00:44:58.200 --> 00:45:01.510
We all did. All of us.
That doesn't mean...

432
00:45:01.720 --> 00:45:07.158
Was Chancellor Gorkon alive
when you first examined him?

433
00:45:07.360 --> 00:45:08.634
Barely.

434
00:45:08.840 --> 00:45:12.594
Now be careful. Doctor.
Have you ever in your past -

435
00:45:12.800 --> 00:45:16.759
- saved patients as barely alive as he?

436
00:45:16.960 --> 00:45:19.918
I didn't have the medical knowledge
I needed for Klingon anatomy.

437
00:45:20.120 --> 00:45:23.317
- I see.
- You where there.

438
00:45:23.520 --> 00:45:28.514
You say you are due for retirement.
May I ask. do your hands shake?

439
00:45:28.720 --> 00:45:30.631
- Objection!
- I was nervous.

440
00:45:32.720 --> 00:45:35.757
No. You were incompetent.

441
00:45:38.480 --> 00:45:40.710
You were incompetent!

442
00:45:40.920 --> 00:45:44.754
Whether deliberately or as a result of
age combined with drink.

443
00:45:44.960 --> 00:45:49.590
- The court will have to determine.
- My God. man. I tried to save him!

444
00:45:50.640 --> 00:45:52.596
I tried to save him.

445
00:45:54.400 --> 00:45:57.949
I was desperate to save him.

446
00:45:58.160 --> 00:46:02.438
He was the last best hope
in the Universe for peace.

447
00:46:02.640 --> 00:46:05.279
The witness is excused.

448
00:46:08.400 --> 00:46:13.997
There we have it. citizens. We have
established the particulars of the crime.

449
00:46:14.200 --> 00:46:18.637
And now we come to the architect of
this tragic affair.

450
00:46:19.160 --> 00:46:23.995
James Tiberius Kirk.

451
00:46:25.840 --> 00:46:29.310
What would your favourite author say.
Captain?

452
00:46:29.520 --> 00:46:33.752
"Let us sit upon the ground and tell
sad stories of the death of kings."

453
00:46:33.960 --> 00:46:37.157
Tell us your sad story. Kirk.

454
00:46:37.360 --> 00:46:42.229
Tell us that you planned to take
revenge for the death of your son.

455
00:46:42.440 --> 00:46:44.158
- That's not true.
- Objection!

456
00:46:44.360 --> 00:46:49.150
Captain Kirk has not been identified
as the assassin.

457
00:46:49.360 --> 00:46:55.356
I offer into the record this excerpt
from the Captain's personal log.

458
00:46:55.960 --> 00:47:01.114
I've never trusted Klingons.
and I never will.

459
00:47:01.320 --> 00:47:04.551
I've never been able to forgive them
for the death of my boy.

460
00:47:08.240 --> 00:47:10.595
Again! Again!

461
00:47:10.800 --> 00:47:14.110
I've never trusted Klingons.
and I never will.

462
00:47:14.800 --> 00:47:18.679
I've never been able to forgive them
for the death of my boy.

463
00:47:21.680 --> 00:47:24.513
Are those your words?

464
00:47:26.880 --> 00:47:29.314
Those words were spoken by me.

465
00:47:32.960 --> 00:47:36.953
Objection! My client's political views
are not on trial.

466
00:47:37.160 --> 00:47:42.757
On the contrary. Captain Kirk's views
are at the very heart of the matter.

467
00:47:42.960 --> 00:47:48.956
His record shows him to be an
insubordinate. unprincipled opportunist -

468
00:47:49.160 --> 00:47:52.311
- with a history of violating the chain of
command whenever it suited him.

469
00:47:52.520 --> 00:47:53.794
Continue.

470
00:47:54.000 --> 00:47:58.198
The record shows that Captain Kirk
once held the rank of Admiral -

471
00:47:58.400 --> 00:48:03.030
- and he was broken for taking matters
into his own hands.

472
00:48:03.240 --> 00:48:07.916
Do you deny being demoted for
these charges. Answer me now!

473
00:48:08.120 --> 00:48:10.588
- I cannot deny it.
- You were demoted?

474
00:48:10.800 --> 00:48:14.793
- For insubordination?
- On occasion. I have disobeyed orders.

475
00:48:15.000 --> 00:48:18.072
Were you obeying
or disobeying orders -

476
00:48:18.280 --> 00:48:20.840
- when you arranged the assassination
of Chancellor Gorkon?

477
00:48:21.040 --> 00:48:23.554
I didn't know about it
until we boarded the ship.

478
00:48:23.760 --> 00:48:28.356
You still deny the Enterprise
fired on Kronos One?

479
00:48:28.560 --> 00:48:32.633
And you still deny your men beamed
aboard and shot the Chancellor?

480
00:48:32.840 --> 00:48:37.197
I cannot confirm or deny
actions which I didn't witness.

481
00:48:37.400 --> 00:48:40.790
Are you aware
that as the captain of a ship. -

482
00:48:41.000 --> 00:48:44.595
- you are responsible for
the actions of your men?

483
00:48:47.080 --> 00:48:48.832
I am.

484
00:48:49.040 --> 00:48:54.637
If it's proved that members of your
crew carried out the assassination...

485
00:48:54.840 --> 00:48:57.593
- They're setting us up. Your Honours!
- Do not answer.

486
00:48:57.800 --> 00:49:02.351
Captain Kirk.
you will answer the question.

487
00:49:09.120 --> 00:49:12.271
As Captain...

488
00:49:12.480 --> 00:49:15.597
...l'm responsible for
the crew under my command.

489
00:49:19.160 --> 00:49:22.118
Your Honours. the state rests.

490
00:49:23.640 --> 00:49:26.916
Send to Commander Enterprise.

491
00:49:27.120 --> 00:49:30.908
"We stand ready to assist you.
Captain Sulu. U.S.S. Excelsior."

492
00:49:31.600 --> 00:49:38.438
It is the determination of this court that
the prisoners are guilty as charged.

493
00:49:49.280 --> 00:49:54.638
I wish to note for the record that
all the evidence is circumstantial.

494
00:49:54.840 --> 00:49:58.389
I beg the court to consider this
when pronouncing its sentence.

495
00:49:58.600 --> 00:50:00.113
So noted.

496
00:50:00.320 --> 00:50:04.108
Captain James T. Kirk.
Dr. Leonard McCoy.

497
00:50:04.320 --> 00:50:07.915
In the interest of fostering amity -

498
00:50:08.120 --> 00:50:14.309
- for the forthcoming peace talks.
the sentence of death is commuted.

499
00:50:21.120 --> 00:50:25.796
It is the judgement of this court -

500
00:50:26.000 --> 00:50:29.959
- that. without possibility
of reprieve or parole. -

501
00:50:30.160 --> 00:50:35.280
- you be taken from this place to
the dilithium mines -

502
00:50:35.480 --> 00:50:39.598
- on the penal asteroid of Rura Penthe.

503
00:50:40.240 --> 00:50:44.995
There to spend the rest of
your natural lives.

504
00:50:52.480 --> 00:50:55.199
Rura Penthe!

505
00:50:56.720 --> 00:51:00.793
Known throughout the galaxy as
the alien's graveyard.

506
00:51:01.000 --> 00:51:04.913
Better to kill them now
and get it over with.

507
00:51:24.120 --> 00:51:28.750
Lieutenant.
The torpedo hit once again. please.

508
00:51:33.480 --> 00:51:35.391
Hold.

509
00:51:36.040 --> 00:51:39.874
It is Enterprise. We fired.

510
00:51:40.080 --> 00:51:45.473
That is not possible! All weapons
visually accounted for. sir.

511
00:51:46.760 --> 00:51:48.352
An ancestor of mine maintained -

512
00:51:48.560 --> 00:51:54.157
- that if you eliminate the impossible.
whatever remains must be the truth.

513
00:51:54.360 --> 00:51:56.476
What does that mean?

514
00:51:56.680 --> 00:52:01.549
That if we cannot have fired
those torpedoes. someone else did.

515
00:52:01.760 --> 00:52:05.514
They didn't fire on themselves
and there are no other ships present.

516
00:52:05.720 --> 00:52:09.269
- There was a neutron surge.
- Not from us.

517
00:52:09.480 --> 00:52:14.270
A neutron surge that big
could only be produced by another ship.

518
00:52:14.480 --> 00:52:17.552
- Kronos One?
- Too far away.

519
00:52:17.760 --> 00:52:21.912
Very near us. Possibly beneath us.

520
00:52:22.120 --> 00:52:26.796
If there were a ship beneath us.
the Klingons would have seen it.

521
00:52:28.440 --> 00:52:30.874
Would they?

522
00:52:32.840 --> 00:52:37.470
- A Bird of Prey?
- A Bird of Prey.

523
00:52:39.080 --> 00:52:43.119
- Cloaked?
- They can't fired when they're cloaked.

524
00:52:43.320 --> 00:52:46.710
All things being equal. I would agree.

525
00:52:46.920 --> 00:52:50.799
However. things are not equal.
This one can.

526
00:52:51.520 --> 00:52:54.353
- We must inform Starfleet Command.
- Of what?

527
00:52:54.560 --> 00:52:59.031
A new weapon that's invisible?
They'll call us raving lunatics.

528
00:52:59.240 --> 00:53:03.836
They'll say we'll say anything
to exonerate the Captain.

529
00:53:04.040 --> 00:53:07.032
And they would be correct.
We have no evidence.

530
00:53:07.240 --> 00:53:10.277
Only a theory
which happens to fit the facts.

531
00:53:10.480 --> 00:53:14.996
Assuming you're right. Why would they
fire on their own President?

532
00:53:15.200 --> 00:53:17.156
Indeed.

533
00:53:17.360 --> 00:53:21.353
This ship will be searched
from bow to stern.

534
00:53:21.560 --> 00:53:25.473
I do not understand.
If there was a ship underneath us -

535
00:53:25.680 --> 00:53:29.719
- surely the assassins beamed aboard
from that vessel. not Enterprise.

536
00:53:29.920 --> 00:53:33.071
You're forgetting something.
Mr Chekov.

537
00:53:33.280 --> 00:53:37.068
According to our data banks.
this ship fired those torpedoes.

538
00:53:37.280 --> 00:53:39.669
If we did. the killers are here.

539
00:53:39.880 --> 00:53:43.919
If we did not.
whoever altered the data banks is here.

540
00:53:44.120 --> 00:53:48.511
In either case.
what we are looking for is here.

541
00:53:48.720 --> 00:53:53.032
- What are we looking for. sir?
- Lieutenant.

542
00:53:54.600 --> 00:53:56.591
Two pairs of gravity boots.

543
00:55:00.000 --> 00:55:03.310
This is the gulag Rura Penthe.

544
00:55:03.520 --> 00:55:10.471
There is no stockades.
no guard tower. no electronic frontier.

545
00:55:11.480 --> 00:55:14.916
Only a magnetic shield
prevents beaming.

546
00:55:15.120 --> 00:55:20.194
Punishment means exile
from prison to the surface.

547
00:55:21.040 --> 00:55:25.716
On the surface. nothing can survive.

548
00:55:29.320 --> 00:55:33.632
Work well. and you will be treated well.

549
00:55:33.840 --> 00:55:38.311
Work badly. and you will die.

550
00:57:00.160 --> 00:57:02.355
Oh. my God!

551
00:57:06.520 --> 00:57:11.469
The universal translator
has been confiscated.

552
00:57:11.680 --> 00:57:13.477
I'm sorry?

553
00:57:17.680 --> 00:57:20.752
He's definitely on about something. Jim.

554
00:57:25.080 --> 00:57:26.559
If this is your spot. we'll move on.

555
00:57:28.040 --> 00:57:30.713
He wants your obedience to
the Brotherhood of Aliens.

556
00:57:30.920 --> 00:57:33.070
- He's got it.
- And your coat.

557
00:57:33.280 --> 00:57:35.157
I'm afraid not. It wouldn't fit.

558
00:57:50.160 --> 00:57:54.233
- Thanks.
- This will help keep you warm.

559
00:57:55.480 --> 00:58:01.191
- I'm Martia. You're Kirk and McCoy.
- How did you know that?

560
00:58:01.400 --> 00:58:03.595
We don't get many
presidential assassins.

561
00:58:03.800 --> 00:58:07.509
- We didn't kill Gorkon.
- Of course not.

562
00:58:07.720 --> 00:58:10.678
- But there's a reward for your death.
- That figures.

563
00:58:11.600 --> 00:58:13.238
We've been set up.

564
00:58:13.440 --> 00:58:16.557
Somebody up there
wants you out of the way.

565
00:58:23.800 --> 00:58:25.358
- Any progress?
- None.

566
00:58:25.560 --> 00:58:30.554
A crew of 300 are looking everywhere.
but the killers may still be among them.

567
00:58:30.760 --> 00:58:34.070
Surely they have disposed of
these boots by now.

568
00:58:34.280 --> 00:58:37.033
Would it not have been logical
to leave them on Gorkon's ship?

569
00:58:37.240 --> 00:58:42.189
Logic must give way to physics. Gravity
wasn't restored when they escaped.

570
00:58:42.400 --> 00:58:46.552
Without the boots. they would have
floated off the transporter pads.

571
00:58:46.760 --> 00:58:49.035
Why not simply vaporize them?

572
00:58:52.000 --> 00:58:53.831
Like this?

573
00:59:00.040 --> 00:59:06.115
As you know. no one can fire an
unauthorized phaser aboard a starship.

574
00:59:07.400 --> 00:59:11.393
Suppose. when they returned.
they threw the boots into the refuse.

575
00:59:11.600 --> 00:59:14.160
I'm having the refuse searched.

576
00:59:14.360 --> 00:59:20.037
If I'm correct. those boots will cling to
the killer's necks like Tiberian bats.

577
00:59:20.240 --> 00:59:24.950
They couldn't escape without them
nor throw them out the window.

578
00:59:25.160 --> 00:59:27.116
Those boots are here. Somewhere.

579
00:59:27.320 --> 00:59:33.270
- Did someone fire off a phaser?
- It's alright. It's nothing.

580
00:59:33.480 --> 00:59:37.758
Mr Spock. Starfleet is screaming for us
to return to port.

581
00:59:37.960 --> 00:59:40.918
- Who fired the...
- Ah. Mr Scott.

582
00:59:41.120 --> 00:59:45.477
I hear you have difficulty with the warp
drive. How long do you need for repair?

583
00:59:45.680 --> 00:59:48.353
There's nothing wrong
with the bloody thing.

584
00:59:48.560 --> 00:59:54.556
If we return to space dock. the killers
can dispose of their footwear -

585
00:59:54.760 --> 00:59:58.673
- and we will never see the Captain
or Dr. McCoy alive again.

586
00:59:58.880 --> 01:00:01.075
- It could take weeks.
- Thank you.

587
01:00:01.280 --> 01:00:05.068
Val'eris. inform Starfleet
our warp drive is inoperative.

588
01:00:05.280 --> 01:00:08.158
- A lie?
- An error.

589
01:00:08.840 --> 01:00:12.958
We have lost all contact
with the Captain and Dr. McCoy.

590
01:00:13.160 --> 01:00:16.994
Yes. at the moment they're surrounded
by a magnetic shield.

591
01:00:17.200 --> 01:00:22.638
But if I know the Captain.
he is deep into planning his escape.

592
01:00:44.600 --> 01:00:46.875
You've got him
where you want him. Jim!

593
01:01:37.800 --> 01:01:39.836
- Are you alright?
- I think so.

594
01:01:40.040 --> 01:01:43.874
- They'll respect you now.
- I was lucky that thing had knees.

595
01:01:44.080 --> 01:01:46.719
That was not his knee.

596
01:01:46.920 --> 01:01:50.515
Not everybody keep their genitals
in the same place. Captain.

597
01:01:50.720 --> 01:01:53.757
Anything you want to tell me?

598
01:01:53.960 --> 01:01:58.954
See what you can do for him. Let him
know we're not holding a grudge.

599
01:01:59.160 --> 01:02:02.755
Suppose he's holding a grudge?

600
01:02:02.960 --> 01:02:09.195
When whoever it is makes their move.
you won't be here to ask if he's the one.

601
01:02:12.400 --> 01:02:15.949
- Do you want to get out of here?
- There's got to be a way.

602
01:02:36.000 --> 01:02:39.231
Three months before retirement.
What a way to finish.

603
01:02:39.440 --> 01:02:43.353
- We're not finished.
- Speak for yourself.

604
01:02:43.560 --> 01:02:46.996
One day. one night... Kobayashi Maru!

605
01:02:47.200 --> 01:02:52.433
Bones! Are you afraid of the future?

606
01:02:52.640 --> 01:02:57.191
I believe that was the general idea
that I was trying to convey.

607
01:02:57.400 --> 01:03:02.599
- I don't mean this future.
- What is this - multiple choice?

608
01:03:02.800 --> 01:03:07.954
Some people are afraid...
of what might happen.

609
01:03:09.560 --> 01:03:14.031
- I was terrified.
- What terrified you. specifically?

610
01:03:20.120 --> 01:03:23.999
No more neutral zone.

611
01:03:24.200 --> 01:03:27.112
I was used to hating Klingons.

612
01:03:29.960 --> 01:03:34.033
It never even occurred to me
to take Gorkon at his words.

613
01:03:36.600 --> 01:03:41.958
- Spock was right.
- We all felt exactly the same.

614
01:03:42.160 --> 01:03:46.472
No. Somebody felt a lot worse.

615
01:03:48.200 --> 01:03:50.589
I'm beginning to understand why.

616
01:03:50.800 --> 01:03:53.997
If you've got any bright ideas.
now is the time.

617
01:03:54.200 --> 01:03:58.591
Time is the problem.
You and I are nothing.

618
01:03:58.800 --> 01:04:01.030
You heard the judge -
the peace conference is on again.

619
01:04:01.240 --> 01:04:05.233
Whoever killed Gorkon is bound to
attempt another assassination.

620
01:04:07.720 --> 01:04:09.790
Unless we can get out of here.

621
01:04:21.000 --> 01:04:26.074
It's me - Martia. Listen. No one has ever
escaped from Rura Penthe.

622
01:04:26.280 --> 01:04:29.556
- Except us.
- It is possible.

623
01:04:29.760 --> 01:04:31.751
I know how to get outside the shield.

624
01:04:31.960 --> 01:04:35.589
- How do we fit in?
- Getting outside the shield is easy.

625
01:04:35.800 --> 01:04:39.998
After that. you have to get us off the
surface before we freeze. Can you?

626
01:04:41.800 --> 01:04:45.793
- It's possible.
- I can't make it alone.

627
01:04:46.000 --> 01:04:49.470
You're the likeliest candidate
to come here for months.

628
01:04:49.680 --> 01:04:53.195
Candidate for what?

629
01:05:05.880 --> 01:05:10.431
Go to lift 7 in the morning
for mining duty. I'll see you there.

630
01:05:10.640 --> 01:05:13.029
Don't disappoint me.

631
01:05:15.000 --> 01:05:18.390
- What is it with you. anyway?
- Still think we're finished?

632
01:05:18.600 --> 01:05:20.477
More than ever.

633
01:05:25.360 --> 01:05:26.918
Sorry to wake you. sir.

634
01:05:27.120 --> 01:05:32.433
Starfleet requests any data we have on
the whereabouts of Enterprise.

635
01:05:34.400 --> 01:05:35.913
What?

636
01:05:36.120 --> 01:05:40.238
They're refusing to acknowledge
signal to return to space dock. sir.

637
01:05:44.000 --> 01:05:48.869
Signal Starfleet that we have no idea
location Enterprise.

638
01:05:49.440 --> 01:05:53.319
- Sir?
- You have hearing problems?

639
01:05:54.000 --> 01:05:55.592
No. sir.

640
01:06:37.120 --> 01:06:39.236
Klingon blood.

641
01:06:39.440 --> 01:06:44.230
They must have walked through it when
it was floating and tracked it back here.

642
01:06:44.440 --> 01:06:47.352
This is the first evidence
which corroborates our theory.

643
01:06:47.560 --> 01:06:49.676
Now we go to Starfleet?

644
01:06:49.880 --> 01:06:53.190
We expand our search
to include uniforms.

645
01:06:53.400 --> 01:06:55.550
All uniforms?

646
01:07:13.800 --> 01:07:16.473
Clear. sir. Make a hole.

647
01:07:16.680 --> 01:07:19.672
Coming through. Coming through.

648
01:07:31.240 --> 01:07:33.470
Sir! Sir!

649
01:08:02.800 --> 01:08:06.475
- I think we've been had.
- No. you weren't. Doctor.

650
01:08:06.680 --> 01:08:10.434
Get off at the first level.
Follow the gang into the mine.

651
01:08:10.640 --> 01:08:13.074
They don't take girls.

652
01:08:22.960 --> 01:08:28.159
- You are crewman Dax?
- Yes. What is the problem?

653
01:08:28.360 --> 01:08:35.072
Perhaps you know
Russian epic of Cinderella?

654
01:08:35.280 --> 01:08:38.909
If shoe fits - wear it.

655
01:08:40.240 --> 01:08:43.391
Mr Chekov...

656
01:08:56.680 --> 01:08:58.557
Watch me.

657
01:09:00.440 --> 01:09:04.877
What kind of creature is this?
Last night you two were...

658
01:09:07.680 --> 01:09:09.955
Get in.

659
01:10:17.120 --> 01:10:19.395
Come on. We don't have a lot of time.

660
01:10:36.480 --> 01:10:38.471
Hurry!

661
01:10:41.680 --> 01:10:43.910
Up there.

662
01:10:45.200 --> 01:10:47.077
Come on - climb!

663
01:10:57.640 --> 01:11:00.518
Here. you'll need these. Quickly!

664
01:11:20.800 --> 01:11:22.756
Stay close.

665
01:12:36.040 --> 01:12:38.759
- There they are.
- They emerge from the beaming shield.

666
01:12:39.400 --> 01:12:44.349
Mr Scott. start your engines.
Mr Chekov. set course for Rura Penthe.

667
01:12:44.560 --> 01:12:48.394
Mr Spock. Rura Penthe is deep inside
the Klingon frontier.

668
01:12:48.600 --> 01:12:50.909
- If we're discovered...
- Correct.

669
01:12:51.120 --> 01:12:55.352
We need a feat of linguistic legerdemain
and intrepidity -

670
01:12:55.560 --> 01:12:58.074
- before the Captain and Dr. McCoy
freeze to death.

671
01:13:05.280 --> 01:13:08.716
- Leave me. I'm finished.
- No!

672
01:13:08.920 --> 01:13:12.879
Bones. I'm wearing
a viridium patch on my back.

673
01:13:13.080 --> 01:13:16.993
Spock slapped it there
before we went on Gorkon's ship.

674
01:13:17.200 --> 01:13:19.589
That cunning little Vulcan.

675
01:13:19.800 --> 01:13:22.792
Come on! We're in the clear.

676
01:13:23.840 --> 01:13:28.277
Now that we're outside the shield.
they can locate us two sectors away.

677
01:13:28.480 --> 01:13:30.391
If they're even looking for us.

678
01:13:59.160 --> 01:14:02.470
This is listening post Morska.

679
01:14:02.680 --> 01:14:04.910
What ship is that. over?

680
01:14:15.440 --> 01:14:19.558
We must respond. A universal
translator would be recognised.

681
01:14:27.960 --> 01:14:31.350
We am thy freighter... Ursva.

682
01:14:31.560 --> 01:14:35.030
Six weeks out of...

683
01:14:35.240 --> 01:14:38.073
...Kronos.

684
01:14:51.720 --> 01:14:54.075
"What is your destination. over?"

685
01:14:58.440 --> 01:15:01.512
We is condemning food...

686
01:15:04.440 --> 01:15:07.079
...things and supplies.

687
01:15:10.560 --> 01:15:14.189
Don't catch any bugs.

688
01:15:44.040 --> 01:15:47.430
Would you mind explaining
that little trick you do?

689
01:15:47.640 --> 01:15:52.270
- I'm a Chameloid.
- I've heard about you.

690
01:15:52.480 --> 01:15:56.632
Shape-shifters.
I thought you were mythical.

691
01:15:57.160 --> 01:15:59.879
Give a girl a chance. Captain.

692
01:16:01.400 --> 01:16:03.391
It takes a lot of effort.

693
01:16:03.600 --> 01:16:05.909
I don't doubt it.

694
01:16:06.120 --> 01:16:08.634
Stop me if I'm wrong. -

695
01:16:08.840 --> 01:16:12.196
- but do we have any way of knowing
whether this is the real you?

696
01:16:12.680 --> 01:16:17.037
I thought I would assume
a pleasing shape.

697
01:16:22.040 --> 01:16:26.318
We're outside the shield.
Now it's your turn. Captain.

698
01:16:26.520 --> 01:16:28.875
If you say so.

699
01:16:29.680 --> 01:16:31.079
Are you crazy?!

700
01:16:31.280 --> 01:16:34.556
She didn't need our help. Where did you
get these convenient clothes?

701
01:16:34.760 --> 01:16:37.832
Don't tell me that flare
is standard prison issue.

702
01:16:38.040 --> 01:16:41.476
It's to let them know where we are.
Ask her what she's getting in return.

703
01:16:41.680 --> 01:16:46.071
A full pardon... which doesn't cover this.

704
01:16:46.280 --> 01:16:49.192
An accident wasn't good enough.
Come on. Spock.

705
01:16:49.400 --> 01:16:53.951
Good enough for one.
Two would have looked suspicious.

706
01:16:54.160 --> 01:16:59.359
Killed while attempting escape.
That's convincing for both.

707
01:17:03.120 --> 01:17:04.678
Surprise!

708
01:17:16.000 --> 01:17:19.072
- Your friends are late.
- They'll be along.

709
01:17:22.160 --> 01:17:25.630
- I can't believe I kissed you.
- Must have been your lifelong ambition.

710
01:17:41.160 --> 01:17:43.230
Isn't it time you became
something else?

711
01:17:43.440 --> 01:17:45.032
I like it here.

712
01:17:53.520 --> 01:17:57.035
Well. well. well...

713
01:18:04.200 --> 01:18:06.873
What took you so long?

714
01:18:07.240 --> 01:18:09.435
Kill him. he's the one.

715
01:18:09.640 --> 01:18:11.392
Not me. you idiot - him!

716
01:18:13.640 --> 01:18:17.110
- No witnesses.
- Killed while trying to escape.

717
01:18:17.800 --> 01:18:20.712
- Damned clever. if you ask me.
- It's a classic.

718
01:18:20.920 --> 01:18:24.071
- That's what he wanted.
- Who? Who wanted us killed?

719
01:18:24.840 --> 01:18:28.879
Since you're all going to die anyway.
why not tell you?

720
01:18:29.080 --> 01:18:30.991
His name is...

721
01:18:36.760 --> 01:18:42.995
Damn it! What the hell! Son of a!
Couldn't you have waited two seconds?

722
01:18:43.200 --> 01:18:45.031
He was about to explain
the whole thing.

723
01:18:45.240 --> 01:18:47.834
- You want to go back?
- Absolutely not!

724
01:18:50.560 --> 01:18:52.949
This is the bridge.
We're still in Klingon space.

725
01:18:53.160 --> 01:18:59.110
Deck 9. remain at battle stations.
Deck 9. remain at battle stations.

726
01:19:30.400 --> 01:19:32.630
They were beamed aboard
a Federation Starship.

727
01:19:32.840 --> 01:19:35.638
I could trace...

728
01:19:40.520 --> 01:19:43.671
Escaped.

729
01:19:44.560 --> 01:19:49.350
Kirk cannot know the location of
the peace conference.

730
01:19:49.800 --> 01:19:51.950
Are you sure?

731
01:19:52.600 --> 01:19:56.275
Will you take that chance?

732
01:19:56.480 --> 01:20:00.234
Helmsman.
make course to intercept Enterprise.

733
01:20:06.320 --> 01:20:09.278
The Klingons have a Bird of Prey
that can fire while cloaked.

734
01:20:09.480 --> 01:20:12.358
- She torpedoed Gorkon's ship.
- So that's it.

735
01:20:12.560 --> 01:20:15.632
We believe that Gorkon's murderers
are aboard this ship.

736
01:20:15.840 --> 01:20:20.152
- Has the peace conference begun?
- Who knows? The location is secret.

737
01:20:20.360 --> 01:20:23.238
- There's always something.
- Captain! Mr Spock!

738
01:20:23.440 --> 01:20:26.637
I found the uniforms
with the Klingon blood on them.

739
01:20:41.200 --> 01:20:46.877
But the uniforms belong to
these two men. Burke and Samno.

740
01:20:47.480 --> 01:20:50.950
Not anymore.
Phaser on "stun" at close range.

741
01:20:51.160 --> 01:20:54.630
First rule of assassination -
kill the assassins.

742
01:20:55.080 --> 01:20:59.551
- Now we're back to square one.
- Can I talk to you?

743
01:21:00.800 --> 01:21:05.828
- Why weren't they vaporized?
- It would set off the alarm.

744
01:21:12.920 --> 01:21:14.831
It's possible.

745
01:21:15.040 --> 01:21:18.715
Now hear this. Now hear this.

746
01:21:18.920 --> 01:21:22.879
Court reporter to sick bay.
Code blue - urgent.

747
01:21:23.080 --> 01:21:26.709
Statements to be taken at once
from Yeomen Burke and Samno.

748
01:21:26.920 --> 01:21:31.072
Repeat. court reporter to sick bay.
Code blue - urgent.

749
01:21:31.280 --> 01:21:33.396
Statements to be taken.

750
01:21:33.600 --> 01:21:38.469
Repeat. statements to be taken from
Yeomen Burke and Samno.

751
01:22:15.040 --> 01:22:16.519
You have to shoot.

752
01:22:20.280 --> 01:22:24.831
If you are logical. you have to shoot.

753
01:22:28.800 --> 01:22:31.075
- I do not want to.
- What you want is irrelevant.

754
01:22:31.280 --> 01:22:34.556
What you've chosen is at hand.

755
01:22:34.760 --> 01:22:36.432
I'd just as soon you didn't.

756
01:22:43.920 --> 01:22:46.275
The operation is over.

757
01:22:51.560 --> 01:22:54.916
I did not fire.
You cannot prove anything.

758
01:22:55.120 --> 01:23:00.035
Yes. I can. At my trial my personal log
was used against me.

759
01:23:00.240 --> 01:23:03.949
How long did you wait outside
my quarters before I noticed you?

760
01:23:05.560 --> 01:23:07.790
You knew?

761
01:23:09.080 --> 01:23:11.719
I tried to tell you.
but you would not listen.

762
01:23:12.800 --> 01:23:15.758
Neither of us was hearing very well
that night.

763
01:23:15.960 --> 01:23:19.350
There were things I tried to tell you.
about having faith.

764
01:23:19.560 --> 01:23:24.190
You have betrayed the Federation.
All of you.

765
01:23:24.400 --> 01:23:27.551
- And what have you've been doing?
- Saving Starfleet.

766
01:23:27.760 --> 01:23:34.279
Klingons cannot be trusted. Sir...
You said so yourself.

767
01:23:34.480 --> 01:23:38.314
They killed your son.
Did you not wish Gorkon dead?

768
01:23:38.520 --> 01:23:42.593
"Let them die". you said.
Did I misinterpret you?

769
01:23:44.720 --> 01:23:46.597
And you were right.

770
01:23:46.800 --> 01:23:50.634
They conspired with us to assassinate
their own Chancellor.

771
01:23:50.840 --> 01:23:53.070
How trustworthy can they be?

772
01:23:53.280 --> 01:23:56.909
Klingons and Federation members
conspiring together.

773
01:23:57.120 --> 01:24:01.238
- Who is "us"?
- All who stands to lose from peace.

774
01:24:01.440 --> 01:24:02.919
Names. Lieutenant.

775
01:24:03.120 --> 01:24:08.319
My comrades will make certain
all your transmissions are jammed.

776
01:24:08.520 --> 01:24:13.548
- Names. Lieutenant!
- I do not remember.

777
01:24:15.800 --> 01:24:18.519
A lie?

778
01:24:18.720 --> 01:24:20.756
A choice.

779
01:24:24.560 --> 01:24:27.120
Spock.

780
01:25:08.280 --> 01:25:12.034
Admiral Cartwright.

781
01:25:12.240 --> 01:25:14.629
From Starfleet?

782
01:25:21.480 --> 01:25:23.948
Who else?

783
01:25:27.120 --> 01:25:31.398
General... Chang.

784
01:25:37.120 --> 01:25:44.196
- Who else?
- Romulan Ambassador and others.

785
01:25:48.080 --> 01:25:50.992
Where is the peace conference?

786
01:25:52.280 --> 01:25:55.113
Where is the peace conference?

787
01:26:27.080 --> 01:26:29.355
She does not know.

788
01:26:30.640 --> 01:26:32.232
Then we're dead.

789
01:26:42.640 --> 01:26:47.395
I have been dead before.
Contact Excelsior.

790
01:26:47.600 --> 01:26:51.479
- She'll have the co-ordinates.
- I've already got it. sir.

791
01:26:52.040 --> 01:26:54.429
- Standing by. Captain Kirk.
- Sulu.

792
01:26:54.640 --> 01:26:59.077
You realize that by even talking to us.
you're violating regulations.

793
01:26:59.280 --> 01:27:01.794
I'm sorry. Captain.
Your message is breaking up.

794
01:27:02.000 --> 01:27:05.549
Bless you. Sulu.
Where is the peace conference?

795
01:27:05.760 --> 01:27:07.318
They'll attempt another assassination.

796
01:27:07.520 --> 01:27:12.310
It's at Camp Khitomer.
near the Romulan border.

797
01:27:12.520 --> 01:27:15.080
I'm sending the co-ordinates on
a coded frequency.

798
01:27:15.280 --> 01:27:17.396
We'll need more than that.

799
01:27:17.600 --> 01:27:21.354
There's a Bird of Prey on the look-out
for us that can fire when cloaked.

800
01:27:21.560 --> 01:27:23.790
Surely not.

801
01:27:24.000 --> 01:27:28.596
How many of those things are there?
Come on. Lieutenant.

802
01:27:28.800 --> 01:27:31.553
- Just the prototype.
- Do you hear that?

803
01:27:31.760 --> 01:27:35.116
I'm getting under way now.
We're in Alpha Quadrant.

804
01:27:35.320 --> 01:27:38.153
The chances of our reaching
the conference in time are slim.

805
01:27:38.360 --> 01:27:43.150
- When does this conference start?
- According to my information - today.

806
01:27:44.560 --> 01:27:47.916
- Thank you. Captain Sulu.
- Don't mention it. Captain Kirk.

807
01:27:54.360 --> 01:27:56.510
Spock?

808
01:27:56.720 --> 01:27:58.836
I prefer it dark.

809
01:28:05.400 --> 01:28:09.632
- Dining on ashes?
- You were right.

810
01:28:09.840 --> 01:28:16.598
It was arrogant presumption on my part
that got us into this situation.

811
01:28:16.800 --> 01:28:20.031
You and the Doctor
might have been killed.

812
01:28:20.240 --> 01:28:22.708
The night is young.

813
01:28:22.920 --> 01:28:27.869
You said it yourself. it was logical.
Peace is worth a few personal risks.

814
01:28:30.800 --> 01:28:32.836
You're a great one for logic.

815
01:28:33.040 --> 01:28:37.875
I'm a great one for rushing in
where angels fear to tread.

816
01:28:38.080 --> 01:28:44.349
We're both extremists. Reality is
probably somewhere in between.

817
01:28:47.960 --> 01:28:50.758
I couldn't get past the death of my son.

818
01:28:50.960 --> 01:28:55.476
I was prejudiced by her
accomplishments as a Vulcan.

819
01:28:55.680 --> 01:28:59.229
Gorkon had to die before I understood
how prejudiced I was.

820
01:29:07.200 --> 01:29:08.918
Is it possible...

821
01:29:09.680 --> 01:29:17.109
...that we two. you and I.
have grown so old and inflexible -

822
01:29:17.320 --> 01:29:21.757
- that we have outlived our usefulness?

823
01:29:21.960 --> 01:29:24.679
Would that constitute a joke?

824
01:29:25.800 --> 01:29:30.112
- It wasn't your fault.
- I was responsible.

825
01:29:30.960 --> 01:29:36.034
- For no actions but your own.
- That's not what you said at your trial.

826
01:29:36.240 --> 01:29:38.470
That was as captain of the ship.
Human beings...

827
01:29:38.680 --> 01:29:41.831
We both know that I am not human.

828
01:29:42.040 --> 01:29:45.510
Do you want to know something?
Everybody's human.

829
01:29:46.360 --> 01:29:50.069
I find that remark... insulting.

830
01:29:50.600 --> 01:29:51.874
Come. I need you.

831
01:29:56.240 --> 01:30:00.711
Madam Chancellor.
members of the diplomatic corps...

832
01:30:01.760 --> 01:30:04.558
...honoured guests.

833
01:30:04.760 --> 01:30:07.957
The United Federation of Planets
welcomes you to Camp Khitomer.

834
01:30:24.000 --> 01:30:26.468
She's out here somewhere.

835
01:30:26.680 --> 01:30:31.356
- But if she's cloaked...
- Then all we have is a radiation surge.

836
01:30:31.560 --> 01:30:36.190
By the time we're close enough
to record it. we're ashes.

837
01:30:38.720 --> 01:30:41.314
2.06...

838
01:30:43.280 --> 01:30:45.111
2.03...

839
01:30:46.160 --> 01:30:52.679
- Close enough to beam down?
- Not yet. In two minutes. 1.58.

840
01:30:52.880 --> 01:30:55.792
Go to impulse power for Khitomer.

841
01:31:04.120 --> 01:31:09.148
Let us redefine progress to mean that
just because we can do a thing -

842
01:31:09.360 --> 01:31:13.990
- it does not necessarily follow
that we must do that thing.

843
01:31:17.240 --> 01:31:19.834
- Uhura?
- Nothing. Captain.

844
01:31:20.040 --> 01:31:22.952
If she's here.
she's rigged for silent running.

845
01:31:29.720 --> 01:31:33.190
Coming up on transporter range
in 57 seconds.

846
01:31:33.400 --> 01:31:36.836
Transporter room.
Stand by to beam down.

847
01:31:39.000 --> 01:31:41.230
53...

848
01:31:44.760 --> 01:31:47.194
48 seconds.

849
01:31:51.240 --> 01:31:53.435
44...

850
01:31:55.360 --> 01:31:58.636
I can see you. Kirk.

851
01:31:58.840 --> 01:32:00.751
Chang.

852
01:32:00.960 --> 01:32:03.315
Can you see me?

853
01:32:03.520 --> 01:32:08.036
Now be honest. Captain.
Warrior to warrior.

854
01:32:08.240 --> 01:32:11.994
You do prefer it this way. don't you?
As it was meant to be.

855
01:32:12.800 --> 01:32:15.360
No peace in our time.

856
01:32:15.560 --> 01:32:20.588
"Once more unto the breach.
dear friends."

857
01:32:35.520 --> 01:32:38.512
- This is fun.
- Reverse engines. All astern.

858
01:32:38.720 --> 01:32:40.790
One and a half impulse power. Back off!

859
01:32:44.880 --> 01:32:47.553
What's she doing?

860
01:32:48.200 --> 01:32:50.760
What's she waiting for?

861
01:32:50.960 --> 01:32:54.635
Probably attempting to ascertain
why we are reversing.

862
01:32:54.840 --> 01:32:57.877
Wondering whether we detect her.

863
01:33:01.920 --> 01:33:03.592
Incoming!

864
01:33:07.520 --> 01:33:09.829
- In range?
- Not yet. sir.

865
01:33:10.040 --> 01:33:11.519
Come on!

866
01:33:11.720 --> 01:33:13.438
- She'll fly apart.
- Fly her apart. then!

867
01:33:13.640 --> 01:33:19.033
Many speculated about
my father's motives.

868
01:33:19.240 --> 01:33:24.189
Some said he was an idealist.
Others said he had no choice.

869
01:33:24.400 --> 01:33:29.758
If Praxis had not exploded. his idealism
wouldn't have found expression.

870
01:33:31.120 --> 01:33:33.236
We are a proud race.

871
01:33:33.440 --> 01:33:37.911
We are here because we intend
to go on being proud.

872
01:33:47.280 --> 01:33:50.955
- Go to auxiliary power!
- Auxiliary circuits destroyed.

873
01:33:56.840 --> 01:34:00.992
"Tickle us. do we not laugh?
Prick us. do we not bleed?"

874
01:34:01.640 --> 01:34:06.031
"Wrong us. shall we not revenge?"

875
01:34:06.240 --> 01:34:07.639
Gas.

876
01:34:09.320 --> 01:34:13.916
Gas. Captain. Under impulse power
she expands fuel. like all vessels.

877
01:34:14.120 --> 01:34:19.353
We call it "plasma".
but it is merely ionised gas.

878
01:34:19.560 --> 01:34:24.236
What about our equipment
to catalogue gaseous anomalies?

879
01:34:26.240 --> 01:34:28.356
The thing's got to have a tail-pipe.

880
01:34:28.560 --> 01:34:32.712
Doctor. would you assist me
in performing surgery on a torpedo?

881
01:34:32.920 --> 01:34:35.115
Fascinating.

882
01:34:36.160 --> 01:34:38.151
Hard to starboard.

883
01:34:39.600 --> 01:34:43.832
The proposed agenda is as follows:
The evacuation of Kronos -

884
01:34:44.040 --> 01:34:47.316
- has been calculated
within the 50 Earth year time span.

885
01:34:47.520 --> 01:34:49.988
Phase 1 - preparation for evacuation...

886
01:34:59.800 --> 01:35:04.828
Captain. she's packing quite a wallop.
Shields weakening.

887
01:35:11.120 --> 01:35:15.989
Shields up! Alright. now we're giving
them something else to shoot at.

888
01:35:22.760 --> 01:35:25.911
The game's afoot.

889
01:35:32.520 --> 01:35:36.752
- Excelsior's been hit!
- "Our revels now are ended". Kirk.

890
01:35:44.800 --> 01:35:50.158
"Cry havoc.
and let slip the dogs of war."

891
01:35:50.680 --> 01:35:54.070
- Bones. where's my torpedo?
- Bet you wished you'd stayed in bed.

892
01:35:56.400 --> 01:35:59.119
Shields collapsing!

893
01:36:00.200 --> 01:36:02.270
The key. please. Time is short.

894
01:36:10.480 --> 01:36:13.040
- The hull has been compromised.
- I wonder how bad.

895
01:36:13.240 --> 01:36:14.719
Connect echo-bars.

896
01:36:14.920 --> 01:36:17.195
...discuss the report on phase 2.

897
01:36:17.400 --> 01:36:20.710
- Alter circuit A.
- Sensor.

898
01:36:20.920 --> 01:36:23.388
...we commence
within minutes of the preparation.

899
01:36:23.600 --> 01:36:28.116
- "I am constant as the Northern star."
- I'd give real money. if he'd shut up.

900
01:36:28.760 --> 01:36:30.034
Plate. please.

901
01:36:30.240 --> 01:36:31.798
...and assimilation will consume...

902
01:36:32.000 --> 01:36:33.911
We've got a heart beat.

903
01:36:35.080 --> 01:36:36.877
...with the Klingon Empire...

904
01:36:37.080 --> 01:36:38.718
Key. please.

905
01:36:38.920 --> 01:36:40.831
- Where's that torpedo?
- She's ready.

906
01:36:41.040 --> 01:36:43.474
Lock and load!

907
01:36:44.840 --> 01:36:46.558
Fire!

908
01:36:58.320 --> 01:37:01.471
"To be... or not"...

909
01:37:02.080 --> 01:37:03.752
..."to be."

910
01:37:05.040 --> 01:37:06.996
Target that explosion and fire.

911
01:37:09.360 --> 01:37:11.237
Fire!

912
01:37:20.520 --> 01:37:24.229
This work will occupy us
throughout most of the week.

913
01:37:24.440 --> 01:37:25.839
I hope that the delegation -

914
01:37:26.040 --> 01:37:32.878
- can implement the provisions
of Phase 1 by the first of next month.

915
01:37:33.080 --> 01:37:36.675
As you know. time is of the essence.

916
01:37:36.880 --> 01:37:38.393
Out of the way!

917
01:37:43.400 --> 01:37:45.118
Mr President!

918
01:37:46.400 --> 01:37:48.356
Mr President!

919
01:37:49.760 --> 01:37:51.591
Kirk. Enterprise.

920
01:37:53.400 --> 01:37:54.992
Protect the Chancellor!

921
01:38:02.080 --> 01:38:05.117
- Arrest those men!
- Arrest yourself!

922
01:38:09.760 --> 01:38:11.910
We've got a full confession.

923
01:38:26.320 --> 01:38:30.438
- This is not Klingon blood.
- Cartwright. Just a minute.

924
01:38:38.400 --> 01:38:40.311
It's Colonel West!

925
01:38:43.800 --> 01:38:47.236
What's happened?
What's the mean of all of this?

926
01:38:47.440 --> 01:38:49.317
It's about the future. Madam Chancellor.

927
01:38:50.200 --> 01:38:55.558
Some people think
the future means the end of history.

928
01:38:55.760 --> 01:38:59.435
We haven't run out of history quite yet.

929
01:38:59.640 --> 01:39:03.838
Your father called the future...

930
01:39:04.040 --> 01:39:08.431
..."the undiscovered country".

931
01:39:09.080 --> 01:39:11.435
People can be
very frightened of change.

932
01:39:16.400 --> 01:39:18.595
You've restored my father's faith.

933
01:39:19.760 --> 01:39:22.718
And you've restored my son's.

934
01:40:08.640 --> 01:40:11.359
Once again. we've saved civilization
as we know it.

935
01:40:11.560 --> 01:40:13.949
And they're not going to prosecute.

936
01:40:14.160 --> 01:40:17.470
They could have prosecuted me.
I felt like Val'eris.

937
01:40:17.680 --> 01:40:20.478
They don't arrest people
for having feelings.

938
01:40:20.680 --> 01:40:25.834
And it's a good thing. too. If they did.
we'd all have to turn ourselves in.

939
01:40:26.880 --> 01:40:30.873
- Captain Kirk.
- Captain Sulu.

940
01:40:31.080 --> 01:40:34.755
As much to the crew of the Enterprise.
I owe you my thanks.

941
01:40:35.360 --> 01:40:40.957
Nice to see you in action one more
time. Captain Kirk. Take care.

942
01:40:52.160 --> 01:40:56.870
- My God. that's a big ship.
- Not so big as her captain.

943
01:40:57.080 --> 01:41:00.675
So... This is goodbye?

944
01:41:01.760 --> 01:41:04.558
It's about time
we got underway ourselves.

945
01:41:04.760 --> 01:41:07.877
Captain. I have orders
from Starfleet Command.

946
01:41:08.080 --> 01:41:13.279
We're to put back to space dock
immediately... to be decommissioned.

947
01:41:27.040 --> 01:41:32.353
If I were human.
I believe my response would be:

948
01:41:32.560 --> 01:41:34.437
"Go to hell."

949
01:41:37.760 --> 01:41:39.398
If I were human.

950
01:41:43.400 --> 01:41:44.913
Course heading. Captain?

951
01:41:51.360 --> 01:41:53.920
Second star to the right.

952
01:41:55.040 --> 01:41:56.951
And straight on 'til morning.

953
01:42:13.760 --> 01:42:17.548
Captain's log. stardate 9529. 1.

954
01:42:17.760 --> 01:42:21.753
This is the final cruise of the Starship
Enterprise under my command.

955
01:42:21.960 --> 01:42:23.791
This ship. and her history-

956
01:42:24.000 --> 01:42:26.798
- will shortly become
the care of another crew.

957
01:42:27.000 --> 01:42:30.709
To them and their posterity
will we commit our future.

958
01:42:30.920 --> 01:42:33.229
They'll continue the voyages
we have begun -

959
01:42:33.440 --> 01:42:35.635
- and journey
to all the undiscovered countries -

960
01:42:35.840 --> 01:42:40.675
- boldly going where no man.
where no one...

961
01:42:40.880 --> 01:42:43.519
...has gone before.
